1
00:07:22,589 --> 00:07:24,798
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">You wished
to speak to me, Doctor?</font>

2
00:07:24,966 --> 00:07:27,384
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">Have you seen Mrs. Vogler yet,
Sister Alma?</font>

3
00:07:27,510 --> 00:07:28,510
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">No, not yet.</font>

4
00:07:28,637 --> 00:07:30,721
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">Let me explain her situation</font>

5
00:07:30,847 --> 00:07:34,475
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">and why you've been
hired to care for her.</font>

6
00:07:35,435 --> 00:07:37,936
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">Mrs. Vogler is an actress,
as you know.</font>

7
00:07:38,063 --> 00:07:41,440
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">In the middle of her last
performance of Electra,</font>

8
00:07:41,941 --> 00:07:46,153
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">she fell silent and looked
around as if in surprise.</font>

9
00:07:46,279 --> 00:07:48,906
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">She was silent
for over a minute.</font>

10
00:08:01,753 --> 00:08:04,338
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">She apologized
to her colleagues afterward,</font>

11
00:08:04,506 --> 00:08:07,174
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">saying she'd felt
a sudden urge to laugh.</font>

12
00:08:07,509 --> 00:08:09,677
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">The next day
the theater called</font>

13
00:08:09,844 --> 00:08:12,596
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">to ask if she'd forgotten
about rehearsal.</font>

14
00:08:12,722 --> 00:08:16,350
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">The maid went in her room
and found her still in bed.</font>

15
00:08:16,518 --> 00:08:19,770
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">She was awake but wouldn't
answer questions or move.</font>

16
00:08:20,980 --> 00:08:23,774
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">This condition's gone on
for three months now.</font>

17
00:08:23,900 --> 00:08:26,652
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">She's been given
every conceivable test.</font>

18
00:08:26,945 --> 00:08:28,862
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">The result is clear:</font>

19
00:08:28,988 --> 00:08:32,491
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">She's perfectly healthy,
both mentally and physically.</font>

20
00:08:32,617 --> 00:08:36,328
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">And it's not a question
of some hysterical reaction either.</font>

21
00:08:36,454 --> 00:08:38,914
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">Any questions,
Sister Alma?</font>

22
00:08:39,374 --> 00:08:43,127
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">If not, you can go
see Mrs. Vogler now.</font>

23
00:08:51,177 --> 00:08:53,220
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">Hello, Mrs. Vogler.</font>

24
00:08:54,723 --> 00:08:56,682
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">I'm Sister Alma.</font>

25
00:08:56,808 --> 00:09:00,310
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">I've been hired to take care
of you for a while.</font>

26
00:09:02,480 --> 00:09:05,482
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">Perhaps I should tell you
a bit about myself.</font>

27
00:09:05,608 --> 00:09:08,235
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">I'm 25 years old,
and I'm engaged.</font>

28
00:09:08,528 --> 00:09:11,697
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">I got my nursing certificate
two years ago.</font>

29
00:09:12,699 --> 00:09:15,075
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">My parents have
a farm in the country.</font>

30
00:09:15,910 --> 00:09:19,455
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">My mother was a nurse too,
before she got married.</font>

31
00:09:21,166 --> 00:09:24,918
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">I should go get your dinner tray...
fried liver and fruit salad.</font>

32
00:09:25,128 --> 00:09:27,171
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">It looked quite good.</font>

33
00:09:27,922 --> 00:09:31,842
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">Shall I raise this end up?
Are you all right like that?</font>

34
00:09:38,433 --> 00:09:42,060
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">Sister Alma,
what's your first impression?</font>

35
00:09:43,021 --> 00:09:45,689
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">I don't know
what to say, Doctor.</font>

36
00:09:46,107 --> 00:09:49,526
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">At first her face looks soft,
almost childish,</font>

37
00:09:49,652 --> 00:09:51,987
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">but then
you see her eyes...</font>

38
00:09:52,530 --> 00:09:54,948
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">Her expression's so hard.</font>

39
00:09:55,825 --> 00:09:57,826
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">Perhaps I shouldn't...</font>

40
00:09:57,952 --> 00:10:00,120
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">What were you going to say?</font>

41
00:10:00,413 --> 00:10:02,956
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">I was thinking I should
turn down the assignment.</font>

42
00:10:03,082 --> 00:10:05,626
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">Why? Did something
frighten you?</font>

43
00:10:05,794 --> 00:10:07,878
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">No, not exactly,</font>

44
00:10:08,004 --> 00:10:11,715
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">but perhaps Mrs. Vogler
should have an older nurse,</font>

45
00:10:11,841 --> 00:10:13,884
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">one with more life experience.</font>

46
00:10:14,010 --> 00:10:17,304
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">I might not be able to manage.
- Manage? In what way?</font>

47
00:10:17,430 --> 00:10:19,640
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">- Mentally.
- Mentally?</font>

48
00:10:20,266 --> 00:10:24,102
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">If she's made a conscious
decision not to speak or move,</font>

49
00:10:24,229 --> 00:10:26,647
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">which must be the case,
since she's healthy...</font>

50
00:10:26,773 --> 00:10:28,398
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">Then?</font>

51
00:10:28,525 --> 00:10:31,735
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">Then that shows
great mental strength.</font>

52
00:10:31,861 --> 00:10:33,862
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">I may not be up to it.</font>

53
00:10:35,824 --> 00:10:38,534
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">I thought you might want
to see the twilight.</font>

54
00:10:38,660 --> 00:10:40,702
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">I can draw
the curtains later.</font>

55
00:10:43,665 --> 00:10:45,707
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">Shall I turn on the radio?</font>

56
00:10:45,959 --> 00:10:48,210
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">I think there's a play on.</font>

57
00:10:50,046 --> 00:10:52,673
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">Forgive me, darling.</font>

58
00:10:53,132 --> 00:10:55,968
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">You must forgive me.</font>

59
00:10:56,135 --> 00:10:59,888
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">All I want
is your forgiveness.</font>

60
00:11:01,266 --> 00:11:05,519
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">What are you laughing about?
ls the actress so funny?</font>

61
00:11:06,187 --> 00:11:10,274
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">What do you know
of mercy? Well?</font>

62
00:11:11,776 --> 00:11:14,278
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">What do you know
of mercy?</font>

63
00:11:19,284 --> 00:11:22,160
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">I don't understand
those sorts of things.</font>

64
00:11:22,954 --> 00:11:25,122
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">I enjoy films
and the theater,</font>

65
00:11:25,248 --> 00:11:27,875
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">but I'm afraid
I don't go very often.</font>

66
00:11:28,042 --> 00:11:31,044
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">I have tremendous
admiration for artists.</font>

67
00:11:31,713 --> 00:11:35,799
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">I think art is enormously
important in life,</font>

68
00:11:35,925 --> 00:11:40,053
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">especially for those struggling
for one reason or another.</font>

69
00:11:41,472 --> 00:11:46,143
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">But I'm skating on thin ice,
telling you about such things.</font>

70
00:11:46,436 --> 00:11:48,812
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">Let's see
if I can find some music.</font>

71
00:11:50,148 --> 00:11:51,899
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">Is that all right?</font>

72
00:11:54,694 --> 00:11:56,987
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">Good night, then.
Sleep well.</font>

73
00:13:48,224 --> 00:13:50,100
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">Damn it.</font>

74
00:13:58,026 --> 00:13:59,735
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">It's funny.</font>

75
00:14:00,403 --> 00:14:02,988
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">You can go about
as you please...</font>

76
00:14:03,740 --> 00:14:06,074
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">doing almost anything
you please.</font>

77
00:14:09,120 --> 00:14:12,664
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">I'll marry Karl-Henrik
and we'll have a couple kids,</font>

78
00:14:12,790 --> 00:14:14,833
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">whom I'll raise.</font>

79
00:14:15,793 --> 00:14:18,879
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">It's all decided.
It's inside me.</font>

80
00:14:19,714 --> 00:14:22,257
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">I don't even have
to think about it.</font>

81
00:14:23,384 --> 00:14:25,635
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">It's a great feeling
of security.</font>

82
00:14:26,763 --> 00:14:29,931
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">I have a job
I like and enjoy.</font>

83
00:14:31,225 --> 00:14:32,934
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">That's good too...</font>

84
00:14:33,686 --> 00:14:35,771
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">but in another way.</font>

85
00:14:36,647 --> 00:14:38,398
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">But it's good.</font>

86
00:14:38,900 --> 00:14:40,400
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">Yes...</font>

87
00:14:42,278 --> 00:14:43,904
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">it's good.</font>

88
00:14:51,412 --> 00:14:54,498
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">I wonder what's really
wrong with her.</font>

89
00:14:57,418 --> 00:14:59,419
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">Elisabet Vogler.</font>

90
00:16:40,605 --> 00:16:43,523
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">Mrs. Vogler, would you like me
to open the letter?</font>

91
00:16:50,573 --> 00:16:52,449
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">Shall I read it?</font>

92
00:16:58,331 --> 00:17:00,457
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">Shall I read it to you?</font>

93
00:17:08,966 --> 00:17:10,759
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">"Dearest Elisabet,</font>

94
00:17:11,260 --> 00:17:14,721
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">since I'm not allowed
to see you, I'm writing instead.</font>

95
00:17:14,889 --> 00:17:18,683
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">If you don't wish to read
my letter, you can ignore it.</font>

96
00:17:20,561 --> 00:17:25,232
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">But I can't help trying
to contact you this way,</font>

97
00:17:25,399 --> 00:17:28,735
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">as I'm tormented
by a persistent question:</font>

98
00:17:28,945 --> 00:17:31,571
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">Have I done you harm
in some way?</font>

99
00:17:31,697 --> 00:17:34,658
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">Have I unknowingly
hurt you somehow?</font>

100
00:17:35,534 --> 00:17:39,579
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">Was there some terrible
misunderstanding between us?"</font>

101
00:17:45,711 --> 00:17:48,171
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">Should I really go on?</font>

102
00:17:56,555 --> 00:17:59,766
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">"As far as I know,
we've been happy recently.</font>

103
00:17:59,892 --> 00:18:01,893
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">Surely we've never been...</font>

104
00:18:02,603 --> 00:18:04,437
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">so close.</font>

105
00:18:05,982 --> 00:18:08,608
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">Do you remember saying,</font>

106
00:18:08,901 --> 00:18:11,194
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">'I'm only just beginning
to understand</font>

107
00:18:11,320 --> 00:18:13,571
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">what it means
to be married'?</font>

108
00:18:13,698 --> 00:18:15,699
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">'You've taught me..."'</font>

109
00:18:16,367 --> 00:18:18,451
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">I can't make it out.</font>

110
00:18:19,287 --> 00:18:22,122
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">"'You've taught..." '
Now I see.</font>

111
00:18:22,498 --> 00:18:26,001
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">"'You've taught me
that we must see each other</font>

112
00:18:26,127 --> 00:18:29,045
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">as two anxious children</font>

113
00:18:29,171 --> 00:18:33,174
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">full of goodwill
and the best of intentions</font>

114
00:18:33,884 --> 00:18:37,595
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">but gov... "'
Now I see.</font>

115
00:18:37,722 --> 00:18:42,142
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">"'...governed by forces
we can only partially control.'</font>

116
00:18:42,852 --> 00:18:45,478
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">Do you remember
saying all that?</font>

117
00:18:46,939 --> 00:18:49,316
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">We were walking
in the woods,</font>

118
00:18:49,442 --> 00:18:52,360
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">and you stopped and grabbed
the belt of my coat..."</font>

119
00:19:00,536 --> 00:19:03,496
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">There was a picture
with the letter.</font>

120
00:19:04,332 --> 00:19:08,001
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">A picture of your son.
I don't know if...</font>

121
00:19:08,961 --> 00:19:11,046
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">Do you want it,
Mrs. Vogler?</font>

122
00:19:13,007 --> 00:19:15,216
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">He looks awfully cute.</font>

123
00:19:47,500 --> 00:19:50,418
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">Elisabet, I don't think
there's any point</font>

124
00:19:50,544 --> 00:19:52,962
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">in your staying here
in the hospital.</font>

125
00:19:53,172 --> 00:19:55,256
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">It's just hurting you
to be here.</font>

126
00:19:55,383 --> 00:19:57,550
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">Since you don't want
to go home,</font>

127
00:19:57,676 --> 00:19:59,844
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">I suggest you
and Sister Alma move out</font>

128
00:19:59,970 --> 00:20:02,055
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">to my summer place
by the sea.</font>

129
00:20:04,225 --> 00:20:06,559
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">You think
I don't understand?</font>

130
00:20:07,061 --> 00:20:09,854
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">The hopeless dream
of being.</font>

131
00:20:09,980 --> 00:20:12,273
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">Not seeming to be,
but being.</font>

132
00:20:14,402 --> 00:20:18,321
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">Conscious and awake
at every moment.</font>

133
00:20:19,573 --> 00:20:22,742
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">At the same time, the chasm
between what you are to others</font>

134
00:20:22,910 --> 00:20:24,953
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">and what you are
to yourself.</font>

135
00:20:25,079 --> 00:20:28,331
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">The feeling of vertigo,
and the constant hunger</font>

136
00:20:28,457 --> 00:20:31,084
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">to be unmasked
once and for all.</font>

137
00:20:31,877 --> 00:20:35,255
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">To be seen through,
cut down...</font>

138
00:20:36,048 --> 00:20:38,258
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">perhaps even annihilated.</font>

139
00:20:39,718 --> 00:20:43,221
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">Every tone of voice a lie,
every gesture a falsehood,</font>

140
00:20:43,347 --> 00:20:45,390
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">every smile a grimace.</font>

141
00:20:46,434 --> 00:20:48,685
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">Commit suicide?</font>

142
00:20:49,145 --> 00:20:51,938
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">No, too nasty.</font>

143
00:20:53,023 --> 00:20:55,108
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">One doesn't do
things like that.</font>

144
00:20:55,234 --> 00:20:58,611
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">But you can refuse
to move or talk.</font>

145
00:20:58,863 --> 00:21:00,989
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">Then at least
you're not lying.</font>

146
00:21:01,115 --> 00:21:04,534
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">You can cut yourself off,
close yourself in.</font>

147
00:21:04,660 --> 00:21:06,870
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">Then you needn't
play any roles,</font>

148
00:21:06,996 --> 00:21:09,914
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">wear any masks,
make any false gestures.</font>

149
00:21:10,040 --> 00:21:12,041
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">So you might think...</font>

150
00:21:12,710 --> 00:21:14,961
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">but reality plays
nasty tricks on you.</font>

151
00:21:15,379 --> 00:21:18,298
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">Your hiding place
isn't watertight enough.</font>

152
00:21:18,466 --> 00:21:21,301
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">Life oozes in from all sides.</font>

153
00:21:24,597 --> 00:21:26,723
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">You're forced to react.</font>

154
00:21:27,933 --> 00:21:31,060
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">No one asks
whether it's genuine or not,</font>

155
00:21:31,187 --> 00:21:33,897
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">whether you're lying
or telling the truth.</font>

156
00:21:34,023 --> 00:21:37,108
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">Questions like that
only matter in the theater,</font>

157
00:21:37,234 --> 00:21:39,277
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">and hardly even there.</font>

158
00:21:40,571 --> 00:21:42,655
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">I understand you,
Elisabet.</font>

159
00:21:42,781 --> 00:21:45,909
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">I understand that you're
not speaking or moving,</font>

160
00:21:46,494 --> 00:21:50,497
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">that you've turned this apathy
into a fantastic setup.</font>

161
00:21:51,373 --> 00:21:53,833
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">I understand
and admire you.</font>

162
00:21:55,127 --> 00:21:59,172
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">I think you should play this part
until it's played out,</font>

163
00:21:59,882 --> 00:22:02,258
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">until it's no longer
interesting.</font>

164
00:22:02,384 --> 00:22:06,012
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">Then you can drop it,
just as you eventually drop</font>

165
00:22:06,847 --> 00:22:08,973
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">all your other roles.</font>

166
00:22:13,187 --> 00:22:16,314
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">Thus, at the end of the summer,
Mrs. Vogler and Sister Alma</font>

167
00:22:16,440 --> 00:22:18,858
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">move out to the doctor's
summer house.</font>

168
00:22:19,026 --> 00:22:23,071
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">The stay by the sea agrees
very well with the actress.</font>

169
00:22:23,739 --> 00:22:26,074
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">Her crippling apathy
at the hospital</font>

170
00:22:26,200 --> 00:22:29,077
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">gives way to long walks,
fishing excursions,</font>

171
